# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BAUER GROUP Console Security Banner — local deployment secrets
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Copy this file to `.env` in the repo root. `.env` is gitignored.
# 2. Fill in the four Cloudflare/R2 values below.
# 3. Run `npm run deploy:dry` to preview, `npm run deploy` to push.
#
# In CI (GitHub Actions), set the same names under:
#   Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → Repository secrets
# (or use an organization-level secret shared with the Microsites repo —
#  the values are identical: same R2 account + same Cloudflare zone).
#
# Push local .env values to GitHub secrets with: npm run secrets:push
#
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare R2 + CDN  (zone: console-banner-cf)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The `cloudflare` provider uploads to R2 bucket `bg-widgets` (prefix
# `console-banner/`) AND purges the matching URLs on the Cloudflare zone so
# clients get the new bytes before the edge TTL expires.
#
# Needs four values:
#   1. R2 S3 access key + secret  (R2 → Manage R2 API Tokens)
#   2. Cloudflare API token       (My Profile → API Tokens → Zone.Cache Purge)
#   3. Cloudflare zone ID         (professional-hosting.com → API sidebar → Zone ID)
#
# widgets.professional-hosting.com lives in the professional-hosting.com
# Cloudflare zone, so CF_ZONE_ID + CF_PURGE_TOKEN are identical to the
# Microsites deploy; R2_* come from the same R2 account.
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
CF_PURGE_TOKEN=
CF_ZONE_ID=
